  "_doc": "Cross-port option-parity contract. Every logical option below MUST exist in all six ports' options definitions (any listed alias, normalized = lowercased with non-alphanumerics stripped). This is the guard that would have caught the JS disableTools/disableSkills drift. Add an option => add a row here; the checker fails CI if any port lacks it. Aliases cover legitimate per-port idioms (JS fetch = Python http_transport = Go HTTPClient = the one logical 'http client' option).",
